Colin Wood reports: At least one municipal government was among those to see their internet service disrupted after a cyberattack against a Maine telecommunications firm Sunday caused an outage affecting 23 towns along the state’s midcoastal region. A local NBC affiliate reported that the government office of Damariscotta, a tourist town of roughly 2,300 inhabitants, known for...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F07%2F21%2Fcyberattack-against-maine-telecom-disrupted-municipal-internet-service-in-23-towns%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dcyberattack-against-maine-telecom-disrupted-municipal-internet-service-in-23-towns&amp;action_name=Cyberattack%20against%20Maine%20telecom%20disrupted%20municipal%20internet%20service%20in%2023%20towns&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
<p><a href="https://databreaches.net/2026/07/21/cyberattack-against-maine-telecom-disrupted-municipal-internet-service-in-23-towns/?pk_campaign=feed&#038;pk_kwd=cyberattack-against-maine-telecom-disrupted-municipal-internet-service-in-23-towns">Source</a></p>

