Milford, New Hampshire is a quintessential New England town. But charm is no defense against cyberattackers, and it appears that the town may have been attacked last week. As DysruptionHub was the first to report, the town began experiencing problems early on July 15.  Town email alerts, shared with DataBreaches by a town resident, reveal...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F07%2F21%2Fmilford-new-hampshire-confirms-unauthorized-activity-withholds-details-of-suspected-cyberattack%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dmilford-new-hampshire-confirms-unauthorized-activity-withholds-details-of-suspected-cyberattack&amp;action_name=Milford%2C%20New%20Hampshire%20Confirms%20Unauthorized%20Activity%2C%20Withholds%20Details%20of%20Suspected%20Cyberattack%20%281%29&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
<p><a href="https://databreaches.net/2026/07/21/milford-new-hampshire-confirms-unauthorized-activity-withholds-details-of-suspected-cyberattack/?pk_campaign=feed&#038;pk_kwd=milford-new-hampshire-confirms-unauthorized-activity-withholds-details-of-suspected-cyberattack">Source</a></p>

