Camellia Burris reports: One Middle Tennessee school district is delaying the start of the school year due to a data breach in its computer network. School officials in Sumner County discovered the breach in its computer network earlier this week and subsequently revised the district calendar so the problem could be resolved before students return...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F07%2F22%2Ftn-data-breach-delays-start-of-sumner-county-school-year%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dtn-data-breach-delays-start-of-sumner-county-school-year&amp;action_name=TN%3A%20Data%20breach%20delays%20start%20of%20Sumner%20County%20school%20year&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
<p><a href="https://databreaches.net/2026/07/22/tn-data-breach-delays-start-of-sumner-county-school-year/?pk_campaign=feed&#038;pk_kwd=tn-data-breach-delays-start-of-sumner-county-school-year">Source</a></p>

